notes.text: I’ve used the 80/20 rule here. In reality, There will be use cases for having the entire clinical statement (or ActStatement) here instead of just an observation. On the other hand, we can probably deal with 80% of the use cases by just having an observation here.
Only more than one id if the identifier root is being re-mapped or also sending version or view ids.

constraints.text: Context AllEntities inv: id.reliability != “UNV” inv: id.scope != “BUSN”

attribute.name: id
attribute.description: This identifies the primary object identifier for the role as used by the authoring system of the instance. Multiple repetitions are allowed to support conveying "version" and "snapshot" ids where these are necessary. In rare circumstances (where a system migration is taking place), multiple "object" identifiers may be sent to support transition. However, alternate identifiers must not be sent in this structure. Use IdentifiedEntity for alternate identifiers.
